main event: A civilian observer reported a round object hovering over the horizon near Georgetown, Alabama on January 7, 1966.
interesting points: The object had a diameter of about 30-50 feet and hovered 5 feet above the ground,It emitted a sound like a turbine engine and occasionally a green light at the bottom,The observer's watch stopped at the time of the sighting,The object accelerated rapidly and disappeared after a few seconds,The observer was noted to be a reliable, 18-year-old student from Alabama.
sighted object: a round object with a diameter of 30-50 feet
